`getContentSize` and `getDimensions` return different sizes:

**`getContentSize()`** â€” Returns the actual rendered size of the text:
```typescript
const size = label.getContentSize();
// size.width = actual pixel width of rendered text
// size.height = actual pixel height of rendered text
```

**`getDimensions()`** â€” Returns the bounding box set by `setDimensions`:
```typescript
label.setDimensions(200, 100);
const dims = label.getDimensions();
// dims.width = 200, dims.height = 100 (the set constraints)
```

If no dimensions are set, `getDimensions()` returns (0, 0), while `getContentSize()` returns the auto-calculated text size.

```typescript
const label = cc.Label.createWithSystemFont('Hello', 'Arial', 24);
// getDimensions() â†’ (0, 0) â€” no constraints
// getContentSize() â†’ (~60, ~28) â€” actual text size

